    <element name="Duality Domain" type="Archetype" source="Omeria" id="ID_DMDAVE_OMERIA_ARCHETYPE_CLERIC_DUALITY">
        <supports>Divine Domain</supports>
        <description>
            <p>Omerian powers whose portfolios include duality are usually chaotic or neutral deities who waver between two opposing ideologies. Sometimes these powers are extremists who do not believe that there is a middle ground—it’s either black or white, life or death, total destruction or unbroken peace. Others believe that every situation deserves a fresh view. After all, the cosmos is a complicated place.</p>
            <p class="indent">The two most popular powers devoted to duality in Omeria are Usteus, the God of Judgment, and Ohm, the Elemental God of Water.</p>
            <p class="indent">A cleric who follows a god of duality does not gain features from a single domain as most clerics do. Instead, when creating your duality cleric, you must choose a dichotomy from the list below. Each dichotomy lists a pair of opposing domains from which you gain your powers.</p>
            <p class="indent">At the start of each day after you complete a long rest, you must decide which of the two domains you wish to draw your power from for that day. Once you select a domain, you only gain the benefits and features of that domain until you complete another long rest, at which point you may choose the opposing domain or keep the same domain.</p>
            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr><td>Domain 1</td><td>Domain 2</td></tr>
                </thead>
                <tr><td>Death</td><td>Life</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Death</td><td>Twilight</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Destruction</td><td>Order</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Nature</td><td>Forge</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Order</td><td>Trickery</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Peace</td><td>War</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Peace</td><td>Tempest</td></tr>
            </table>
        </description>
        <sheet>
            <description>At the start of each day after you complete a long rest, you must decide which of the two domains you wish to draw your power from for that day. Once you select a domain, you only gain the benefits and features of that domain until you complete another long rest, at which point you may choose the opposing domain or keep the same domain.</description>
        </sheet>
        <rules>
            <select name="Duality Dichotomies" type="Archetype Feature" supports="dualitydomainpair" level="1" />
        </rules>
    </element>
